sv:property.sv:value: eXo Platform is an out-of-the-box social intranet solution. Rich collaboration features such as wikis, forums, calendars and documents are smartly integrated around activity streams, social networking and workspaces.
eXo began as an open source project in 2002, as the industry's first Java portlet container. The eXo Project catalyzed a portal market dominated by a handful of very large vendors.

Mashup technology empowers web developers to become agents of Service-Oriented Architecture (SOA) within an enterprise, creating situational applications that can solve many unique business problems.Â
